Vice President Mike Pence participated in a discussion with over 50 governors to provide an update on the work of the White House Coronavirus Task Force. The discussion aimed to coordinate efforts with state and local officials in responding to and preparing for the coronavirus. Pence thanked the governors and state and local health officials for their leadership. The Vice President, along with HHS Secretary Alex Azar and CDC Principal Deputy Director Dr. Anne Schuchat, provided a status update on the coronavirus and discussed ongoing federal efforts. Governor Larry Hogan, Chair of the National Governors Association, joined Pence in person, while other governors joined via video teleconference or phone. Pence pledged to convene weekly teleconferences with the governors and assured them of continued coordination between federal leaders and state and local leaders.